== About

This specification describes the APDU messages interface to communicate with the Bitcoin
application.
== Wallet usage APDUs

=== GET WALLET PUBLIC KEY
==== Description

This command returns the extended public key for the given BIP 32 path. The base58check-encoded public key, together with the derivation path, can be verified on-screen.

==== Coding

'Command'

[width="80%"]
|==============================================================================================================================
| *CLA* | *INS*  | *P1*               | *P2*       | *Lc*     | *Le*   
|   E1  |   00   |  00 : do not display the pubkey

                    01 : display the pubkey

                 |  00
|==============================================================================================================================

'Input data'

[width="80%"]
|==============================================================================================================================
| *Description*                                                                     | *Length*
| Number of BIP 32 derivations to perform (max 10)                                  | 1
| First derivation index (big endian)                                               | 4
| ...                                                                               | 4
| Last derivation index (big endian)                                                | 4
|==============================================================================================================================

'Output data'

[width="80%"]
|==============================================================================================================================
| *Description*                                                                     | *Length*
| Public Key length                                                                 | 1
| Extended public key                                                               | var
|==============================================================================================================================


=== GET ADDRESS
==== Description

This command returns the public for the given BIP 32 path.
The Base58 encoded address can be displayed on the device screen.

==== Coding

'Command'

[width="80%"]
|==============================================================================================================================
| *CLA* | *INS*  | *P1*               | *P2*       | *Lc*     | *Le*   
|   E1  |   01   |  00 : do not display the address

                    01 : display the address

                 |  01 : return a legacy P2PKH address

                    02 : return a native segwit address P2WPKH (bech32)

                    03 : return a wrapped segwit address, P2SH-P2WPKH address

|==============================================================================================================================

'Input data'

[width="80%"]
|==============================================================================================================================
| *Description*                                                                     | *Length*
| Number of BIP 32 derivations to perform (max 10)                                  | 1
| First derivation index (big endian)                                               | 4
| ...                                                                               | 4
| Last derivation index (big endian)                                                | 4
|==============================================================================================================================

'Output data'

[width="80%"]
|==============================================================================================================================
| *Description*                                                                     | *Length*
| Bitcoin address length                                                            | 1
| Bitcoin address                                                                   | var
|==============================================================================================================================


